climbs.name: Twerk Life
climbs.fa: Ian Cb or possibly someone else

content.description: On the right side of the left of the fruit boulders, start from a sit on good edges right next to each other.  Move left through a small edge with a sharp thumb catch, then go huge left to a gaston feature and take it to the top.  This is essentially a link up of Apples and Bananas and Low Hanging Fruit.  A foot on the kicker was used, but not the detached blocks.

Start as for Low Hanging Fruit, matched on a right facing sidepull.  Pull on (without the blocks for feet), make a long move right to a pinch, sort your feet, move through a crimp and another cool pinch, then finish right on better holds above Apples and Bananas.  You BETTER not dab on that tree.
content.protection: I did it with one big pad
content.location: The Fruit problems.  100 feet north of a "Baraboo Quartzite" sign on the Tumbled rocks trail, and 80 feet up the hill.  This is on the left boulder, and starts on the left and trends right.

content.description: Same start position as Strawberry Jam. Bump to the crimp out left then either move your right hand to a side pull or crimp before bumping up to the large sloper hold on Peaches and top out above.
Start on the right side of the boulder on an obvious ledge / pocket.  move left through crimps, crossing over peaches. Finish on the upper left side of the boulder.
content.location: same boulder as peaches. photo to follow.

content.description: Start low with left hand on a crimp rail and right hand on an undercling. Climb out the bulge and up the boulder.
content.location: 75 - 100 feet off the tumbled rocks trail, 100 feet south of Big Red. Better description and photo to follow.

content.description: Start on a good sidepull rail and climb up the arete through a couple moves on very cool edges and pinches.
content.location: A few feet left of Apples and Bananas.  This cluster of boulders is in the trees before the Group Leader talus field, maybe 50 feet up from the trail.

content.description: Start with good right hand and heel hook. Bump up to good left hold then make a big move around the right arete and pop to the top
Start on two opposing crimps/rails on a small buldge with good feet.  Make a big move to a lip sloper, shuffle feet and gain better holds on the top slab/face.  Top out.
content.location: About 75-100 feet off the Tumbled Rocks Trail, near Big red.  Better description of location to come.  3-5 new problems in this small boulder cluster.  Photos to come.

pathTokens: 4.  Peaches and Castle in the Sky

content.description: Boulders that form an inside corner. In the woods, not too far above the Tumbled Rocks Trail.
